title: Facebook says it is removing, flagging false claims over West Coast fires
text: Facebook Inc. FB, -0.55% says it is fighting a wave of misinformation from false claims on its platform that antifa activists were setting blazes on the West Coast.

title: Understanding Corporate Denial
text: A noted cynic in the 1920s had described the corporation as an ingenious device for delivering individual profit without individual responsibility.

title: Big Tech is turning on one another amid antitrust probes and litigation
text: “Battle royale” evokes images of professional wrestlers engaged in a free-for-all brawl in which combatants eventually turn on one another until there is an eventual winner. With apologies to Hulk Hogan and Andre the Giant, Big Tech is taking on the same trappings as companies turn on one another amid multiple antitrust investigations and issues.

title: Instagram CEO Says Potential TikTok Ban 'Very Bad For Us'
text: Instagram's newest feature, Reels, is seeing a lot of momentum, especially in India where rival platform TikTok is banned.

title: Facebook Takes Irish Regulator to Court Over Data Transfer Ban
text: The ramifications of the policy decision would affect thousands of companies doing business overseas.

title: Facebook to give employees paid time off to staff polls for election, report says
text: With an expected shortage of poll workers for the general election in November, Facebook will reportedly pay employees who take time off to work at voting sites.

title: Facebook seeks fresh legal delay to block order to suspend its transatlantic data transfers
text: Facebook is firing up its lawyers to try to block EU regulators from forcing it to suspend transatlantic data transfers in the wake of a landmark ruling by Europe’s top court this summer. The tech giant has applied to judges in Ireland to seek a judicial review of a preliminary suspension order, it has emerged.

title: Facebook launches poll worker recruitment push in the News Feed
text: With the election looming and a pandemic still raging through the U.S., a shortage of poll workers is just one of many threats to voting this November — but it’s a big one.

title: The Grand Irony Behind Facebook’s Decision To Invent Facebook All Over Again
text: Facebook, the social network that began as a college meeting ground, has a new feature that's only for college kids. This underscores an uncomfortable reality for Facebook: It's not an app that young people really use anymore.

title: Facebook takes legal action after Irish regulator threatens to clamp down on transatlantic data transfers
text: Facebook has applied to seek a judicial review of the approach used by Ireland's Data Protection Commission in order to reach its decision.

title: Spain aims to tax services like Whatsapp based on revenue
text: Spain is proposing to tax companies providing calls and instant messaging services, such as Whatsapp, based on their revenue, a senior government official said on Friday.

text: Instagram CEO Adam Mosseri said the company will make a case against the planned change to the Apple's iPhone operating system that would impact how it tracks users. But, he said, "I don't think we have much influence over Apple.

title: Facebook to give employees paid time off to vote, staff voting stations
text: The company is also launching a prompt at the top of users' News Feeds to encourage people to sign up to work the polls.

title: Facebook to give paid time off to employees who volunteer as poll workers
text: Facebook will give additional paid time off to employees who volunteer as poll workers during the election, company CEO Mark Zuckerberg said Friday.

title: Head of Instagram weighs in on White House's effort to ban TikTok from the U.S.
text: Any short-term benefit that Instagram would see from a potential TikTok ban is "greatly outweighed by the risks of a fragmented internet," Instagram head Adam Mosseri told CNBC's Andrew Ross Sorkin on Friday.

title: Facebook launches legal action against Irish watchdog over data transfers
text: Facebook Inc launched legal action on Friday against Ireland's Data Protection Commission in an attempt to end a proposed order that could stop it from transferring data from the European Union to the United States.

title: Facebook Snitches On Apple's Alleged Antitrust Behavior To EU Authorities
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) in a filing with the European Union on Tuesday — as a part of a consultative process on the proposed Digital Services Act — accused Apple Inc (NASDAQ: AAPL) of engaging in anticompetitive behavior.
